<div class="wrapper wrapper-padding clearfix">
    <div class="col-1 about homepage-content">
        <h2>About</h2>
        <hr>
        <p>Hello and thank you for stopping by. My name is Charles.</p>
        
        <p>I'm a <a href="http://www.makersacademy.com/">Makers Academy</a> graduate and former Senior Network Administrator. I'm also a Rubyist, Rails admirer, Test Driven Development advocate and overal technology explorer. My aim is to learn at least one new thing every single day.</p>

        <p>I am a natural explorer. I like to find out how things work and what makes them tick. I enjoy putting things apart and putting them back together. Though sometimes I am left with a few "spare" bits. But that does not happen only to me, does it? </p>
        <p><%= link_to 'Read more', welcome_show_path %></p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-2 homepage-content">
        <h2>Things I've written</h2>
        <hr>
        <% @posts.each do |post| %>
        <h3><a href="#"><%= link_to post.title, post %></a></h3>
        <p class="date"><%= post.created_at.strftime('%A, %d %b %Y') %></p>
        <hr>
        <% end %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-3 homepage-content">
        <h2>Things I've built</h2>
        <hr>
        <% @projects.each do |project| %>
            <h3><a href="#"><%= link_to project.title, project %></a></h3>
            <p class="date"><%= project.created_at.strftime('%A, %d %b %Y') %></p>
            <hr>
        <% end %>
    </div>
</div>